item.title: The Weekly Commit #7
item.description: I spotted a wild Big O application!;exciting since I’ve only experienced it as an exercise. Exciting because it clicked, I didn’t simply see that maybe I could write something better, I could prove it was better, given certain conditions and I knew why. I’ll post the rough outline here so I can ask more knowledgeable people how close(or far off) I was and why. Naive `for i in x: for j, k in enumerate(y): if i == k: result.
